MZANSI is regarded as a source and destination country for human trafficking!Addressing a workshop on human trafficking in Tshwane yesterday, deputy minister of justice John Jeffery said men, women and children are being subjected to forced labour and sex work. &ldquo;South African children are recruited from poor rural areas to urban areas, where girls are subjected to sex trafficking and domestic work.&ldquo;Boys are forced to work in street vending, food services and agriculture. &ldquo;Some are forced to beg or commit crime.&rdquo; He said law enforcers reported that traffickers lured victims into the sex trade by forced drug use. Jeffery said a UN report found that Sub-Saharan Africa reported the highest share of child trafficking in the world, with girls and boys more or less equally affected.